    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-21T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="1034"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/7–2154: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-21T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 21, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 718. Repeated information Paris 128,
                    Saigon 97. <persName corresp="#p_OR1">Offroy</persName> of French <gloss
                        target="#t_Del1">del</gloss> tells us that following conclusion of
                    conference today he is pursuing negotiations with Viet Minh <gloss
                        target="#t_Del1">del</gloss> regarding protection of French economic
                    interests in North Vietnam and regarding conditions under which Frenchmen will
                    be allowed to continue to reside there. According to <persName corresp="#p_OR1"
                        >Offroy</persName> French do not propose for present to have any sort of
                    official representation in North Vietnam after evacuation French Expeditionary
                    Corps and have rejected Viet Minh proposal for Viet Minh representation in
                    Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
